22 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 47-30.2-24 of the North Dakota Century Code is
23 amended and reenacted as follows:
24 47-30.2-24. (404) Retention of records by holder.
25 1. A holder required to file a report under section 47-30.2-21 shall retain records for ten
26 years after the later of the date the report was filed or the last date a timely report was
27 due to be filed, unless a shorter period is provided by rule of the commissioner.
28 2. Upon receipt of a notice for an examination or notice of authorization to participate in
29 the voluntary disclosure program under section 47-30.2-55, a holder shall retain, until
30 the conclusion of the examination or any related appeal or litigation, or the conclusion
31 of authorized voluntary disclosure in each instance, all relevant records dating back
