14 bank checks, on which the holder is directly liable, a record of the instruments
15 while they remain outstanding indicating the state and date of issue; and
16 f. Records of items that were not reported as unclaimed sufficient to determine
17 whether the holder has complied with this chapter.
18 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 47-30.2-32 of the North Dakota Century Code is
19 amended and reenacted as follows:
20 47-30.2-32. (603) Payment or delivery of property to administrator.
21 1. Except as otherwise provided in this section, on filing a report under section
22 47-30.2-21, the holder shall pay or deliver to the administrator the property described
23 in the report.
24 2. If property in a report under section 47-30.2-21 is an automatically renewable deposit
25 and a penalty or forfeiture in the payment of interest would result from paying the
26 deposit to the administrator at the time of the report, the date for payment of the
27 property to the administrator is extended until a penalty or forfeiture no longer would
28 result from payment, if the holder informs the administrator of the extended date.
29 3. If property reported to the administrator under section 47-30.2-21 is a security, the
30 administrator may:
