1 a. Make an endorsement, instruction, or entitlement order on behalf of the apparent
2 owner to invoke the duty of the issuer, the transfer agent of the issuer, or the
3 securities intermediary to transfer the security; or
4 b. Dispose of the security under section 47-30.2-41.
5 4. If the holder of property reported to the administrator under section 47-30.2-21 is the
6 issuer of a certificated security, the administrator may obtain a replacement certificate
7 in physical or book-entry form under section 41-08-38. An indemnity bond is not
8 required.
9 5. The administrator shall establish procedures for the registration, issuance, method of
10 delivery, transfer, and maintenance of securities delivered to the administrator by a
11 holder.
12 6. An issuer, holder, or transfer agent acting under this section under instructions of and
13 on behalf of the issuer or holder is not liable to the apparent owner for, and shall be
14 indemnified by the state against, a claim arising with respect to property after the
15 property has been delivered in good faith to the administrator.
16 7. A holder is not required to deliver to the administrator a security identified by the
17 holder as a non-freely transferable security. If the administrator or holder determines
18 that a security is no longer a non-freely transferable security, the holder shall deliver
19 the security on the next regular date prescribed for delivery of securities under this
20 chapter. The holder shall make a determination annually whether a security identified
21 in a report filed under section 47-30.2-21 as a non-freely transferable security is no
22 longer a non-freely transferable security.
23 8. If property reported to the administrator is virtual currency, the holder shall liquidate
24 the virtual currency and remit the proceeds to the administrator. The liquidation must
25 occur anytime within thirty days before the filing of the report under section
26 47 - 30.2 - 21. The owner may not have recourse against the holder or the administrator
27 to recover any gain in value occurring after the liquidation of the virtual currency under
28 this subsection.
