1 47-30.2-39. (610) Periods of limitation and repose.
2 1. Expiration before, on, or after July 1, 2021, of a period of limitation on an owner's right
3 to receive or recover property, whether specified by contract, statute, or court order,
4 does not prevent the property from being presumed abandoned or affect the duty of a
5 holder under this chapter to file a report or pay or deliver property to the administrator.
6 2. The administrator may not commence an action or proceeding to enforce this chapter
7 with respect to the reporting, payment, or delivery of property more than seven years
8 after the holder filed a nonfraudulent report under section 47-30.2-21 with the
9 administrator. The parties may agree in a record to extend the limitation in this
10 subsection.
11 3. The administrator may not commence an action, proceeding, or examination with
12 respect to a duty of a holder under this chapter more than ten years after the duty
13 arose.
14 4. The periods of limitation established by this section are tolled by the earlier of the
15 administrator's delivery of a notice that a holder is subject to an examination or the
16 delivery of notice of authorization to voluntarily disclose property subject to this
17 chapter under section 47-30.2-55.
18 SECTION 5. AMENDMENT. Section 47-30.2-50 of the North Dakota Century Code is
19 amended and reenacted as follows:
20 47-30.2-50. (903) Claim for property by person claiming to be owner.
21 1. A person claiming to be the owner of property held under this chapter by the
22 administrator may file a claim for the property and the claim must be on a form
23 prescribed by the administrator. The claimant shall verify the claim as to the claim's
24 completeness and accuracy.
25 2. The administrator may waive the requirement in subsection 1 and may pay or deliver
26 property directly to a person if:
27 a. The person receiving the property or payment is shown to be the apparent owner
28 included on a report filed under section 47-30.2-21; and
29 b. The administrator reasonably believes the person is entitled to receive the
30 property or payment; and
31 c. The property has a value as provided by rules adopted by the commissioner.
